<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<!--
  Minimal entitlements for an UNSANDBOXED local development build.

  Daybrief ships as a Developer-ID, unsandboxed menu-bar app (it needs a
  loopback HTTP listener for the Google OAuth PKCE flow, which the App Sandbox
  network-server entitlement does not cover for arbitrary 127.0.0.1 ports, plus
  unrestricted Keychain + Application Support access). The App Sandbox key is
  therefore intentionally absent (defaults to off).

  Hardened Runtime + the associated entitlements (e.g.
  com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit if ever needed) and notarization are a later
  release task — see docs/build. This dev build is signed ad-hoc / unsigned.
-->
<dict>
</dict>
</plist>
